; Ginnie Springs Underwater Cave System
; High Springs, Florida, USA
; Approximate centreline survey for SAR planning / educational use.
; Based on published dive reports and cave diving literature.
; NOT a navigational survey — always dive with current certified surveys.
;
; Cave stats (published):
;   Max depth: ~30 m / 97 ft
;   Total surveyed: ~3,000 m
;   Visibility: typically 15-30 m (can drop to zero in disturbed passages)
;   Flow: mild outflow from spring vent
;   Type: freshwater (first-magnitude spring)
;
; SAR NOTES:
;   - The Lips restriction limits equipment size beyond station L0
;   - Twins A/B branch at station M10; parallel routes reconnect
;   - Side passages have silty floors — zero visibility if disturbed
;   - Guideline always present on main passage

*begin ginnie_springs

*title "Ginnie Springs Underwater Cave System"

; Field order: from  to  tape(m)  compass  clino  left  right  up  down
*data normal from to tape compass clino left right up down

; ── BALLROOM (entrance cavern, 5-8 m depth) ─────────────────────────────────
; Large domed cavern at spring vent. Daylight zone extends ~15 m in.
B0    B1    6.2   045   -3   5.5   6.0   2.8   1.5
B1    B2    5.8   050   -5   6.0   6.5   3.0   1.8
